Last updated: April 28, 2026

0. Our core principle
SmartTime collects minimal data. Most data stays on your device.

1. Data we collect

  Account data (stored in Cloud):
    • Email address
    • Display name
    • Profile photo URL
    • Account creation date
  This data is used only for authentication and account management.

  App category preferences (stored in cloud):
    • Your classification of apps as Productive, Neutral, or Distracting
  Stored under your account to sync across devices.

2. Data we do NOT collect
  User data we do NOT collect
  • Document content
  • Screenshots or recordings
  • Keystrokes or mouse activity
  • Any analytics or advertising data
  Activity data (stored locally only):
    • Application name
    • Process name
    • Session start and end time
    This data is stored locally on your device and never uploaded.
  Local settings (stored locally only):
    • App preferences such as refresh interval and idle threshold
3. How we use data
  • To provide account access
  • To sync preferences across devices
  • To enable productivity tracking locally
4. Data sharing
  We do not sell or share your data.
  Data is only processed by Firebase (Google) for authentication and storage for .
5. Data deletion
  You can delete your activity data at any time from within the App.
  You can delete your account, which removes all cloud data associated with it.
6. Security
  We take reasonable measures to protect your data.
  However, no system is completely secure.
7. Age
  This App is not intended for users under the age of 13.
8. Updates
  The App may check for updates via GitHub.
  Your IP address may be visible to GitHub during this process.
9. Contact
  For privacy questions, contact via Github.
